codeword cycling between different re-transmissions of both small and large delay CDD. In addition, an open-loop codeword cycling method for space-frequency block coding, as well as its extension to hybrid ARQ are proposed. In one method, a plurality of information bits are encoded, scrambled and modulated to generate a plurality of modulated symbols. The plurality of modulated symbols is mapped onto the subcarriers in at least one transmission layer of a transmission resource. The modulated symbols are then precoded by using a matrix for cyclic delay diversity and a set of codewords from a certain codebook to generate a plurality of precoded symbols. The codewords are cycled for every N subcarriers. Finally, the precoded symbols are transmitted via a plurality of transmission antennas.
